    "html": "<div style=\"position:relative;width:100%;height:100%;background:var(--surface-dark);background-color:var(--surface-dark);overflow:hidden;\">\n            <div style=\"background: var(--texture-grain); position: absolute; z-index: 1; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; opacity: 0.04\"></div>\n            \n            <div class=\"slide-content\" style=\"position:relative;z-index:10;padding:80px 44px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;height:100%;width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;overflow:hidden;\">\n                <div style=\"width:100%;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;text-align:center;gap:var(--space-2);\"><img src=\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500648767791-00dcc994a43e?w=100\" alt=\"Anonymous Skeptic\" style=\"width:72px;height:72px;border-radius:50%;object-fit:cover;border:3px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.16);\"><p style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:28px;font-weight:800;color:#ECEEF5;line-height:1.2;margin:0;\">\u201cI dismissed this as a toy. Then I tried it. Then I couldn&#x27;t go back to my old workflow. The speed difference isn&#x27;t incremental \u2014 it&#x27;s a different category.\u201d</p><div><div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:15px;font-weight:900;color:#ECEEF5;\">Anonymous Skeptic</div><div style=\"font-family:Plus Jakarta Sans;font-size:12px;color:#CACDD8;\">Now a Regular User</div></div></div>\n            </div>\n        </div>",
